                                    <a class="nav-link" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#StreamRoleConfig" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="StreamRoleConfig" >Configuration</a>
                                </li>
                                <li class="nav-item">
                                    <a class="nav-link" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#StreamRoleExample" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="StreamRoleExample" >Example</a>
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>

                        <div class="collapse" id="StreamRoleDescription" data-parent="#accordionExample">
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <p class="card-text">
                                    This lets you add a role to someone who goes live on Twitch and remove it when they are done.  
                                    Take the new role and put it on the top of the list so everyone knows when someone is hosting a stream.
                                    At least now you have something else to watch on that second monitor when you are not paying attention to your own game. 
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="collapse" id="StreamRoleConfig" data-parent="#accordionExample" >
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <div class="form-check">
                                    <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" value="" id="defaultCheck1">
                                    <label class="form-check-label" for="defaultCheck1">
                                        Enabled
                                    </label>
                                </div>

                                <div class="form-group">
                                    <label for="exampleFormControlSelect1">Select text-channel to send the messages to:</label>
                                    <select class="form-control" id="exampleFormControlSelect1">
                                    <option>1</option>
                                    <option>2</option>
                                    <option>3</option>
                                    <option>4</option>
                                    <option>5</option>
                                    </select>
                                </div>

                                <button type="button" class="btn btn-info">Save</button>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="collapse" id="StreamRoleExample" data-parent="#accordionExample" >

                        </div>
                    </div>

                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="collapse" id="StreamAnnouncer">
            <div class="col-12" class="collapse" id="StreamAnnouncer">
            <div class="card">
                <h5 class="card-header text-center color-disabled">Stream Announcer</h5>
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="text-center">Description</h5>
                    <p class="card-text">
                        With this module you are able to announce to a defined text channel when someone on the server goes live on Twitch.
                    </p>

                    <div class="collapse" id="StreamAnnouncerConfig">
                        <hr>
                        <h5 class="text-center">Config</h5>

                        <div class="form-check">
                            <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" value="" id="defaultCheck1">
                            <label class="form-check-label" for="defaultCheck1">
                                Enabled
                            </label>
                        </div>

                        <div class="form-group">
                            <label for="exampleFormControlSelect1">Select text-channel to send the messages to:</label>
                            <select class="form-control" id="exampleFormControlSelect1">
                            <option>1</option>
                            <option>2</option>
                            <option>3</option>
                            <option>4</option>
                            <option>5</option>
                            </select>
                        </div>

                        <div class="form-check">
                            <input class="form-check-input" type="checkbox" value="" id="defaultCheck1">
                            <label class="form-check-label" for="defaultCheck1">
                                Delete messages on stream conclusion
                            </label>
                        </div>

                        <button type="button" class="btn btn-info">Save</button>

                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="card-footer">
                    <a class="btn btn-link btn-block" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#StreamAnnouncerConfig" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="StreamAnnouncerConfig" >Manage Module</a>
                </div>
            </div>
